'''Aide-mémoire''' is a [[List of French expressions in English|French loanword]] meaning "a memory-aid; a reminder or memorandum, especially a book or document serving this purpose".

In [[international relations]], an '''aide-mémoire''' ({{IPA-fr|ɛdmemwaʁ}}, ''memory aid'') is a proposed agreement or negotiating text circulated informally among delegations for discussion without committing the originating delegation's country to the contents. It has no identified source, title, or attribution and no standing in the relationship involved. Such a text is also referred to as a '''non-paper''' in many international organizations, including the [[General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade]]/[[World Trade Organization]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.enhancedif.org/en/file/291/download?token=JlSPv1g_ |title=AIDE MEMOIRE INTEGRATED FRAMEWORK DIAGNOSTIC STUDY – YEMEN PRELIMINARY VISIT FEBRUARY 4 –13, 2002. (yemen_am.pdf)|format=pdf |publisher=Enhanced Integrated Framework |accessdate=18 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://forum-menschenrechte.de/cms/upload/PDF/ab_05-2008/aides_memoires/Vietnam-IGFM.pdf|title=Aide-Mémoire 7th Session of the UN Human Rights Council 3rd to 28th March 2008|publisher=International Society Human Rights (ISHR)}}</ref> and sometimes within the [[European Union]].<ref>http://www.eda.admin.ch/eda/en/home/doc/publi/pdipl/abctxz.html</ref>

